                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17210712-57-off281 t17210712-57-cd282"></join> last, of which he languished till the 25th, and then Died
            </rs>. It appeared that the Prisoner and the Deceased were intimate Friends, and had been in Company together most past of the Day; that walking together about the Fountain in the <placeName id="t17210712-57-crimeloc283">Middle Temple</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17210712-57-crimeloc283" type="placeName" value="Middle Temple"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17210712-57-crimeloc283" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17210712-57-off281 t17210712-57-crimeloc283"></join> about 9 at Night, a Difference happen'd between them, and they went down to the Library-Door, drew their Swords and fought between that and the First Fruits-Office, and were both Wounded: that when the Surgeon came to them to the Gremers Coffee House, the Prisoner desired him to dress the Deceased first and Deceased desired him to dress the Prisoner first; so that then seemed no manner of Resentment. That the Deceased had 4 wounds, that in the Belley near The Navel was Mortal. That the Prisoner had a wound in the Left Pap, stretching it to the Left Shoulder. It not appearing that there was any premeditated Malice, but that it arose from a sudden. Heart of Passion; and a great many Gentlemen appearing to the Reputation of the Prisoner, and his quit and peaceable Behaviour. The Jury found him <rs id="t17210712-57-verdict284" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17210712-57-verdict284" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
